{
  "texts": [
    "To calculate numeric accuracy, we rely on the simplifying assumption that categories within safety taxonomies often overlap.",
    "For example, content containing profane or disturbing language may also qualify as hate speech or violence.",
    "Based on this intuition, we compile and group fine-grained categories into broader themes.",
    "We provide this map in the Appendix A.10.",
    "Based on this grouping, we assess the accuracy of category predictions for unsafe samples, labeling them as correct or incorrect depending on whether they fall within the same theme as the ground truth."
  ]
}